cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about a neural framework for distant supervised relation extraction, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new self-attention mechanism and uses entity-aware word embeddings, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves classification and information retrieval tasks, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
